/-!
# Parametric dual-span at K_{3,3}^{(c)} ‚ÄĒ Direction C scaffolding

‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ **Dual-span scaffolding for the upper-bound
side of the c-counter at K_{3,3}^{(c)}.**
‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ‚ėÖ

Companion to `V33EnrichedParametric` (which establishes the lower
bound `codim ‚Č• c` via c independent Ōą-discriminators).  This file
builds the SPAN structure needed for the matching upper bound
`codim ‚Č§ c`:

  ¬∑ `psi_layer_linear` ‚ÄĒ Ōą_m is F‚āā-linear over pointwise XOR
  ¬∑ `weighted_e_sum b` ‚ÄĒ the F‚āā-linear combination
    `ő£_m (b m) ¬∑ e_face_layer m`, a c-dim subspace of EnrichedFaceVal
  ¬∑ `psi_layer_weighted_e_sum` ‚ÄĒ Ōą_{m'}(weighted_e_sum b) = b m'
    (Ōą-vector hits any target ‚üĻ ő® : EnrichedFaceVal ‚Üí (Fin c ‚Üí Bool)
    is surjective)
  ¬∑ `psi_projection v` / `psi_residual v` ‚ÄĒ canonical decomposition
    of v as `psi_projection v ‚äē psi_residual v`, with the projection
    in `weighted_e_sum`-form and the residual in the joint
    Ōą-kernel.
  ¬∑ `InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary` ‚ÄĒ F‚āā-linear span of PRIMARY
    cup-products `cupOpp_param (starS i m) ő≤` (left factor an
    S-star) and `cupOpp_param őĪ (incidT j m)` (right factor a
    T-incidence), and coboundaries `delta1_enr_param ŌÉ`.  This
    matches the subspace on which Ōą-functionals (as proven in
    `V33EnrichedParametric`) vanish.  The FULL cup-image span
    is NOT in Ōą-kernel ‚ÄĒ see `psi_layer_arbitrary_cup_not_kill`
    (single-edge cup pairs along face diagonals reproduce every
    face indicator, so the full cup-image span = entire
    `EnrichedFaceVal c`).
  ¬∑ `primary_cup_span_soundness_conditional` ‚ÄĒ given Direction B's
    arbitrary-m kill hypotheses, every element of
    `InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary` lies in the joint Ōą-kernel
    (well-definedness of the conditional structure).
  ¬∑ `primary_cup_span_soundness_all_c` ‚ÄĒ UNCONDITIONAL all-c
    soundness `InPrimary ‚äÜ joint Ōą-kernel`, obtained by chaining
    `primary_cup_span_soundness_on_layer` with Direction B's
    closed `parametric_arbitrary_m_full_kill_capstone` from
    `V33EnrichedParametric`.  Generalises
    `primary_cup_span_soundness_c1` (single-layer) to every
    multiplicity.
  ¬∑ `codim_upper_bound_conditional` ‚ÄĒ IF the joint Ōą-kernel is
    contained in `InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary`, THEN every v
    decomposes canonically modulo `InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary`
    into its `weighted_e_sum` representative.  Equivalently, the
    c Ōą-discriminators SPAN the dual of
    `EnrichedFaceVal c / InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary`.

The unconditional `codim ‚Č§ c` against the PRIMARY cup-image
reduces to ONE remaining open piece:
  ¬∑ **Per-layer completeness (HARD direction)** ‚ÄĒ the per-layer
    K_{3,3} fact that 9-element face space modulo (im őī¬Ļ +
    primary cup-image) has dim 1, generated by `e_face_layer m`.
    Layer-disjointness lifts this to ‚ąÄc.

Direction B (arbitrary-m kill) is now closed via
`parametric_arbitrary_m_full_kill_capstone`; the EASY direction
(`primary_cup_span_soundness_all_c`) is now unconditional at
every c.  See `theory/RESEARCH_PLAN.md` ¬ß1.1.

STRICT ‚ąÖ-AXIOM.
-/

namespace E213.Lib.Math.Cohomology.Bipartite.V33EnrichedParametricDualSpan

open E213.Lib.Math.Cohomology.Bipartite.V33EnrichedParametric
open E213.Lib.Math.Cohomology.Infrastructure.BoolXORFold
open E213.Meta.Nat.Beq213

/-! ## ¬ß1 ‚ÄĒ Ōą_m is F‚āā-linear over pointwise XOR

Lifts `psi_layer c m` through the `psiNatPos`-based abstract XOR
fold (see `Infrastructure.BoolXORFold`) so that pointwise XOR
distributes through the Ōą-sum.  `psi_layer_flat` is a `Nat ‚Üí Bool`
view of the 9 face values at layer m. -/

def psi_layer_flat (c : Nat) (m : Fin c) (v : EnrichedFaceVal c) : Nat ‚Üí Bool
  | 0 => v ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü© m
  | 1 => v ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü© m
  | 2 => v ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü© m
  | 3 => v ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü© m
  | 4 => v ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü© m
  | 5 => v ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü© m
  | 6 => v ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü© m
  | 7 => v ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü© m
  | 8 => v ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü© m
  | _+9 => false

theorem psi_layer_eq_psiNatPos (c : Nat) (m : Fin c) (v : EnrichedFaceVal c) :
    psi_layer c m v = psiNatPos 8 (psi_layer_flat c m v) := rfl

theorem psi_layer_flat_xor (c : Nat) (m : Fin c) (v w : EnrichedFaceVal c) (i : Nat) :
    psi_layer_flat c m (fun s t m' => xor (v s t m') (w s t m')) i
      = xor (psi_layer_flat c m v i) (psi_layer_flat c m w i) := by
  match i with
  | 0 => rfl
  | 1 => rfl
  | 2 => rfl
  | 3 => rfl
  | 4 => rfl
  | 5 => rfl
  | 6 => rfl
  | 7 => rfl
  | 8 => rfl
  | _+9 => rfl

theorem psi_layer_linear (c : Nat) (m : Fin c) (v w : EnrichedFaceVal c) :
    psi_layer c m (fun s t m' => xor (v s t m') (w s t m'))
      = xor (psi_layer c m v) (psi_layer c m w) := by
  rw [psi_layer_eq_psiNatPos, psi_layer_eq_psiNatPos, psi_layer_eq_psiNatPos]
  rw [psiNatPos_congr_all 8
       (psi_layer_flat c m (fun s t m' => xor (v s t m') (w s t m')))
       (fun i => xor (psi_layer_flat c m v i) (psi_layer_flat c m w i))
       (psi_layer_flat_xor c m v w)]
  exact psiNatPos_linear 8 (psi_layer_flat c m v) (psi_layer_flat c m w)

/-! ## ¬ß2 ‚ÄĒ `weighted_e_sum`: F‚āā-combination of `e_face_layer` indicators

`weighted_e_sum c b` is supported only at `(s, t, m') = (0, 0, m')`,
where it carries the value `b m'`.  Equivalently the F‚āā-linear
combination `‚äē_{m ‚ąą Fin c} (b m) ¬∑ e_face_layer c m`.

The Ōą-vector image `(Ōą_0(v), ‚Ä¶, Ōą_{c-1}(v))` is FULLY HIT by
`weighted_e_sum`: for any target b, `weighted_e_sum c b` realises
it.  Hence the map ő® : EnrichedFaceVal c ‚Üí (Fin c ‚Üí Bool),
v ‚Ü¶ (m ‚Ü¶ Ōą_m(v)), is SURJECTIVE. -/

def weighted_e_sum (c : Nat) (b : Fin c ‚Üí Bool) : EnrichedFaceVal c :=
  fun s t m' => (decide (s.val = 0) && decide (t.val = 0)) && b m'

theorem psi_layer_weighted_e_sum (c : Nat) (b : Fin c ‚Üí Bool) (m' : Fin c) :
    psi_layer c m' (weighted_e_sum c b) = b m' := by
  unfold psi_layer weighted_e_sum
  cases b m' <;> rfl

/-- Surjectivity of the joint Ōą-vector map.  For any target
    `b : Fin c ‚Üí Bool`, the cochain `weighted_e_sum c b` has
    `(Ōą_0, ‚Ä¶, Ōą_{c-1}) = b` exactly. -/
theorem psi_vector_surjective (c : Nat) (b : Fin c ‚Üí Bool) :
    ‚ąÉ v : EnrichedFaceVal c, ‚ąÄ m' : Fin c, psi_layer c m' v = b m' :=
  ‚ü®weighted_e_sum c b, psi_layer_weighted_e_sum c b‚ü©

/-! ## ¬ß3 ‚ÄĒ Canonical Ōą-decomposition

For every v : EnrichedFaceVal c, define
`psi_projection v := weighted_e_sum c (m ‚Ü¶ Ōą_m v)` and
`psi_residual v := v ‚äē psi_projection v`.  Then:

  ¬∑ `v = psi_projection v ‚äē psi_residual v` (pointwise XOR)
  ¬∑ `Ōą_m(psi_residual v) = false` for all m

So every v decomposes canonically into a c-dim `weighted_e_sum`
representative (carrying the full Ōą-vector data) and a residual
in the joint Ōą-kernel. -/

def psi_projection (c : Nat) (v : EnrichedFaceVal c) : EnrichedFaceVal c :=
  weighted_e_sum c (fun m => psi_layer c m v)

def psi_residual (c : Nat) (v : EnrichedFaceVal c) : EnrichedFaceVal c :=
  fun s t m' => xor (v s t m') (psi_projection c v s t m')

theorem psi_residual_kills_all_psi (c : Nat) (v : EnrichedFaceVal c) (m' : Fin c) :
    psi_layer c m' (psi_residual c v) = false := by
  show psi_layer c m'
      (fun s t m' => xor (v s t m') (psi_projection c v s t m')) = false
  rw [psi_layer_linear c m' v (psi_projection c v)]
  show xor (psi_layer c m' v)
        (psi_layer c m' (weighted_e_sum c (fun m => psi_layer c m v))) = false
  rw [psi_layer_weighted_e_sum c (fun m => psi_layer c m v) m']
  cases psi_layer c m' v <;> rfl

theorem psi_canonical_decomposition (c : Nat) (v : EnrichedFaceVal c)
    (s t : Fin 3) (m' : Fin c) :
    v s t m' = xor (psi_projection c v s t m') (psi_residual c v s t m') := by
  show v s t m'
      = xor (psi_projection c v s t m')
            (xor (v s t m') (psi_projection c v s t m'))
  cases psi_projection c v s t m' <;> cases v s t m' <;> rfl

/-! ## ¬ß4 ‚ÄĒ `InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary`: F‚āā-span of PRIMARY cup-products + őī¬Ļ-image

Inductively defined: closed under coboundaries `delta1_enr_param ŌÉ`,
**primary** cup-products `cupOpp_param (starS i m) ő≤` (left factor
is an S-star) and `cupOpp_param őĪ (incidT j m)` (right factor is a
T-incidence), and pointwise XOR.  This matches exactly the subspace
of `EnrichedFaceVal c` on which the bottom-layer Ōą_0 functional
vanishes (see `psi_layer_kills_cupOpp_S{0,1,2}star_left_at_bottom`,
`psi_layer_kills_cupOpp_T{0,1,2}incid_right_at_bottom`, and
`psi_layer_kills_delta1`).

NOTE: The corresponding **full** cup-image span (`cupOpp_param őĪ ő≤`
for arbitrary edge cochains őĪ, ő≤) is NOT in Ōą-kernel ‚ÄĒ indeed the
full cup-image span equals all of `EnrichedFaceVal c` since every
face indicator is a single cup `cupOpp_param e_a e_b` for a
diagonal edge pair (a, b).  Concrete witness:
`psi_layer_arbitrary_cup_not_kill`. -/

inductive InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary (c : Nat) : EnrichedFaceVal c ‚Üí Prop where
  | zero : InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary c (fun _ _ _ => false)
  | coboundary (ŌÉ : EnrichedEdgeCoch c) :
      InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary c (delta1_enr_param c ŌÉ)
  | starCup (i : Fin 3) (m : Fin c) (ő≤ : EnrichedEdgeCoch c) :
      InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary c (cupOpp_param c (starS c i m) ő≤)
  | incidCup (j : Fin 3) (m : Fin c) (őĪ : EnrichedEdgeCoch c) :
      InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary c (cupOpp_param c őĪ (incidT c j m))
  | xor_add (v w : EnrichedFaceVal c) :
      InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary c v ‚Üí InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary c w ‚Üí
      InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary c (fun s t m => xor (v s t m) (w s t m))
  /-- Closure under pointwise equality.  Used in the HARD direction
      (`joint Ōą-kernel ‚äÜ InPrimary`) where we build a candidate
      `xor_add`-chain that is pointwise ‚ÄĒ but not as a function-literal ‚ÄĒ
      equal to the target.  Without `funext` (which uses `Quot.sound`,
      forbidden by the ‚ąÖ-axiom standard) we need this bridge.  See
      `V33EnrichedParametricDualSpanHard` for the consumer site. -/
  | cong (v w : EnrichedFaceVal c) (h : ‚ąÄ s t m, v s t m = w s t m) :
      InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary c w ‚Üí InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary c v

/-! ## ¬ß4.5 ‚ÄĒ Why PRIMARY (not full) cup-image: counter-example

Concrete witness that Ōą_0 does NOT kill arbitrary cup-products.
The single-edge cochains at edges 0 and 4 form a diagonal of face
(0, 0, 0) (S-pair {0, 1}, T-pair {0, 1}); their cup is the
single-face indicator at (0, 0, 0), which Ōą_0 detects as
true (XOR of one nonzero face).

Consequence: the FULL cup-image span (closing `cupOpp_param őĪ ő≤`
over arbitrary edge cochains őĪ, ő≤ under F‚āā-XOR) is NOT contained
in the joint Ōą-kernel.  Indeed, single-edge cup pairs along face
diagonals reproduce every face indicator, so the full cup-image
span equals all of `EnrichedFaceVal c`.  This is the structural
reason the codim claim must be against the PRIMARY cup-image (one
factor a star or incidence), NOT the full one. -/

theorem psi_layer_arbitrary_cup_not_kill :
    psi_layer 1 ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü©
      (cupOpp_param 1 (fun e => decide (e.val = 0))
                      (fun e => decide (e.val = 4))) = true := by
  unfold psi_layer cupOpp_param diag_pair_param pair_lo pair_hi edge_idx
  decide

/-! ## ¬ß4.6 ‚ÄĒ Conditional soundness of `InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary`

`InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary` is the F‚āā-span of (őī¬ĻŌÉ), arbitrary-m
primary cups (starS i m ‚ą™ ő≤) and (őĪ ‚ą™ incidT j m).  For it to be
contained in the joint Ōą-kernel, we need:

  ¬∑ `Ōą_{m'} kills cupOpp_param (starS c i m) ő≤` for ALL m, m'
    (when m = m', this is `psi_layer_kills_cupOpp_S{i}star_left_at_bottom`
    at m = 0 only ‚ÄĒ Direction B in HANDOFF; when m ‚Č† m', the cup
    has no support at layer m', so Ōą_{m'} = 0 trivially)
  ¬∑ symmetric statement for `incidT j m`

Both reduce to Direction B's open piece (arbitrary-m kill via
Nat.beq cancellation).  Given those hypotheses the soundness
follows by induction + Ōą-linearity (`psi_layer_linear`). -/

/-- `psi_layer` only reads the 9 values `v ‚ü®s,_‚ü© ‚ü®t,_‚ü© m`, so pointwise
    equality of two face cochains implies equal Ōą-evaluations. -/
theorem psi_layer_pw_congr (c : Nat) (m : Fin c) (v w : EnrichedFaceVal c)
    (h : ‚ąÄ s t m', v s t m' = w s t m') :
    psi_layer c m v = psi_layer c m w := by
  unfold psi_layer
  rw [h ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü© m, h ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü© m,
      h ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü© m, h ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü© m,
      h ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü© m, h ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü© m,
      h ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü© m, h ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü© m,
      h ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü© m]

theorem primary_cup_span_soundness_conditional (c : Nat)
    (H_star : ‚ąÄ (m' : Fin c) (i : Fin 3) (m : Fin c) (ő≤ : EnrichedEdgeCoch c),
        psi_layer c m' (cupOpp_param c (starS c i m) ő≤) = false)
    (H_incid : ‚ąÄ (m' : Fin c) (j : Fin 3) (m : Fin c) (őĪ : EnrichedEdgeCoch c),
        psi_layer c m' (cupOpp_param c őĪ (incidT c j m)) = false) :
    ‚ąÄ v, InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary c v ‚Üí
      ‚ąÄ (m' : Fin c), psi_layer c m' v = false := by
  intro v hv
  induction hv with
  | zero => intro m'; unfold psi_layer; rfl
  | coboundary ŌÉ => intro m'; exact psi_layer_kills_delta1 c ŌÉ m'
  | starCup i m ő≤ => intro m'; exact H_star m' i m ő≤
  | incidCup j m őĪ => intro m'; exact H_incid m' j m őĪ
  | xor_add v w _ _ ih1 ih2 =>
      intro m'
      rw [psi_layer_linear]
      rw [ih1 m', ih2 m']
      rfl
  | cong v w h_eq _ ih =>
      intro m'
      rw [psi_layer_pw_congr c m' v w h_eq]
      exact ih m'

/-! ## ¬ß4.7 ‚ÄĒ Unconditional soundness at c = 1 (single layer)

At `c = 1` the parametric index `m : Fin 1` is forced to
`‚ü®0, _‚ü©`, so the conditional hypotheses `H_star` and `H_incid` of
`primary_cup_span_soundness_conditional` reduce to the
bottom-layer kills already proven in `V33EnrichedParametric`
(`psi_layer_kills_cupOpp_S{0,1,2}star_left_at_bottom` and
`psi_layer_kills_cupOpp_T{0,1,2}incid_right_at_bottom`).
Hence the soundness is UNCONDITIONAL at single layer. -/

private theorem fin1_eq_zero (m : Fin 1) : m = ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü© := by
  match m with
  | ‚ü®0, _‚ü© => rfl
  | ‚ü®n+1, h‚ü© =>
      exfalso
      exact absurd (Nat.le_add_left 1 n) (Nat.not_le_of_lt h)

private theorem fin3_cases {P : Fin 3 ‚Üí Prop}
    (h0 : P ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü©) (h1 : P ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü©) (h2 : P ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü©)
    (i : Fin 3) : P i := by
  match i with
  | ‚ü®0, _‚ü© => exact h0
  | ‚ü®1, _‚ü© => exact h1
  | ‚ü®2, _‚ü© => exact h2
  | ‚ü®n+3, h‚ü© =>
      exfalso
      exact absurd (Nat.le_add_left 3 n) (Nat.not_le_of_lt h)

theorem primary_cup_span_soundness_c1 :
    ‚ąÄ v, InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary 1 v ‚Üí
      ‚ąÄ (m' : Fin 1), psi_layer 1 m' v = false :=
  primary_cup_span_soundness_conditional 1
    (fun m' i m ő≤ => by
      rw [fin1_eq_zero m, fin1_eq_zero m']
      refine @fin3_cases
        (fun k => psi_layer 1 ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü©
                  (cupOpp_param 1 (starS 1 k ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü©) ő≤) = false) ?_ ?_ ?_ i
      ¬∑ exact psi_layer_kills_cupOpp_S0star_left_at_bottom 1 (by decide) ő≤
      ¬∑ exact psi_layer_kills_cupOpp_S1star_left_at_bottom 1 (by decide) ő≤
      ¬∑ exact psi_layer_kills_cupOpp_S2star_left_at_bottom 1 (by decide) ő≤)
    (fun m' j m őĪ => by
      rw [fin1_eq_zero m, fin1_eq_zero m']
      refine @fin3_cases
        (fun k => psi_layer 1 ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü©
                  (cupOpp_param 1 őĪ (incidT 1 k ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü©)) = false) ?_ ?_ ?_ j
      ¬∑ exact psi_layer_kills_cupOpp_T0incid_right_at_bottom 1 (by decide) őĪ
      ¬∑ exact psi_layer_kills_cupOpp_T1incid_right_at_bottom 1 (by decide) őĪ
      ¬∑ exact psi_layer_kills_cupOpp_T2incid_right_at_bottom 1 (by decide) őĪ)

/-! ## ¬ß4.8 ‚ÄĒ Cross-layer vanishing (structural piece of Direction B)

For `m ‚Č† m'`, the primary cup `cupOpp_param (starS i m) ő≤` has no
support at layer m' (since `starS i m` evaluates to false at every
layer-m' edge by 9-block disjointness ‚ÄĒ `nine_block_disjoint_op`).
Hence `Ōą_{m'}` automatically kills these cross-layer primary cups.

This closes the CROSS-LAYER half of the soundness hypothesis of
`primary_cup_span_soundness_conditional` UNCONDITIONALLY (for any
c, any layer pair m ‚Č† m').  The remaining open piece is the
on-layer kill (`m = m'` case): extending the bottom-layer
`psi_layer_kills_cupOpp_S{i}star_left_at_bottom` from `m = 0` to
arbitrary `m`, which is Direction B's targeted-`rw` challenge over
`9¬∑m + ‚Ä¶` offsets. -/

theorem starS_layer_disjoint (c : Nat) (i : Fin 3) (m m' : Fin c)
    (h : m.val ‚Č† m'.val) (j k : Fin 3) :
    starS c i m (edge_idx c j k m') = false := by
  have h_mm' : m'.val ‚Č† m.val := Ne.symm h
  have hj : j.val ‚Č§ 2 := Nat.le_of_lt_succ j.isLt
  have hk : k.val ‚Č§ 2 := Nat.le_of_lt_succ k.isLt
  have hi : i.val ‚Č§ 2 := Nat.le_of_lt_succ i.isLt
  have hjk_lt : 3 * j.val + k.val < 9 :=
    Nat.lt_of_le_of_lt (Nat.add_le_add (Nat.mul_le_mul_left 3 hj) hk) (by decide)
  have hi_le_6 : 3 * i.val ‚Č§ 6 := Nat.mul_le_mul_left 3 hi
  have hi_lt_9 : 3 * i.val < 9 := Nat.lt_of_le_of_lt hi_le_6 (by decide)
  have hi1_lt_9 : 3 * i.val + 1 < 9 :=
    Nat.lt_of_le_of_lt (Nat.add_le_add hi_le_6 (Nat.le_refl 1)) (by decide)
  have hi2_lt_9 : 3 * i.val + 2 < 9 :=
    Nat.lt_of_le_of_lt (Nat.add_le_add hi_le_6 (Nat.le_refl 2)) (by decide)
  show ((9 * m'.val + 3 * j.val + k.val == 9 * m.val + 3 * i.val)
        || (9 * m'.val + 3 * j.val + k.val == 9 * m.val + 3 * i.val + 1)
        || (9 * m'.val + 3 * j.val + k.val == 9 * m.val + 3 * i.val + 2)) = false
  rw [Nat.add_assoc (9 * m'.val) (3 * j.val) k.val]
  rw [Nat.add_assoc (9 * m.val) (3 * i.val) 1]
  rw [Nat.add_assoc (9 * m.val) (3 * i.val) 2]
  rw [nine_block_disjoint_op h_mm' hjk_lt hi_lt_9]
  rw [nine_block_disjoint_op h_mm' hjk_lt hi1_lt_9]
  rw [nine_block_disjoint_op h_mm' hjk_lt hi2_lt_9]
  rfl

theorem incidT_layer_disjoint (c : Nat) (j : Fin 3) (m m' : Fin c)
    (h : m.val ‚Č† m'.val) (s t : Fin 3) :
    incidT c j m (edge_idx c s t m') = false := by
  have h_mm' : m'.val ‚Č† m.val := Ne.symm h
  have hs : s.val ‚Č§ 2 := Nat.le_of_lt_succ s.isLt
  have ht : t.val ‚Č§ 2 := Nat.le_of_lt_succ t.isLt
  have hj : j.val ‚Č§ 2 := Nat.le_of_lt_succ j.isLt
  have hst_lt : 3 * s.val + t.val < 9 :=
    Nat.lt_of_le_of_lt (Nat.add_le_add (Nat.mul_le_mul_left 3 hs) ht) (by decide)
  have hj_lt : j.val < 9 := Nat.lt_of_le_of_lt hj (by decide)
  have h3j_lt : 3 + j.val < 9 :=
    Nat.lt_of_le_of_lt (Nat.add_le_add (Nat.le_refl 3) hj) (by decide)
  have h6j_lt : 6 + j.val < 9 :=
    Nat.lt_of_le_of_lt (Nat.add_le_add (Nat.le_refl 6) hj) (by decide)
  show ((9 * m'.val + 3 * s.val + t.val == 9 * m.val + j.val)
        || (9 * m'.val + 3 * s.val + t.val == 9 * m.val + 3 + j.val)
        || (9 * m'.val + 3 * s.val + t.val == 9 * m.val + 6 + j.val)) = false
  rw [Nat.add_assoc (9 * m'.val) (3 * s.val) t.val]
  rw [Nat.add_assoc (9 * m.val) 3 j.val]
  rw [Nat.add_assoc (9 * m.val) 6 j.val]
  rw [nine_block_disjoint_op h_mm' hst_lt hj_lt]
  rw [nine_block_disjoint_op h_mm' hst_lt h3j_lt]
  rw [nine_block_disjoint_op h_mm' hst_lt h6j_lt]
  rfl

theorem cupOpp_starS_cross_layer_zero (c : Nat) (i : Fin 3) (m m' : Fin c)
    (h : m.val ‚Č† m'.val) (ő≤ : EnrichedEdgeCoch c) (s t : Fin 3) :
    cupOpp_param c (starS c i m) ő≤ s t m' = false := by
  unfold cupOpp_param diag_pair_param
  rw [starS_layer_disjoint c i m m' h (pair_lo s) (pair_lo t)]
  rw [starS_layer_disjoint c i m m' h (pair_hi s) (pair_hi t)]
  rw [starS_layer_disjoint c i m m' h (pair_hi s) (pair_lo t)]
  rw [starS_layer_disjoint c i m m' h (pair_lo s) (pair_hi t)]
  rfl

theorem cupOpp_incidT_cross_layer_zero (c : Nat) (j : Fin 3) (m m' : Fin c)
    (h : m.val ‚Č† m'.val) (őĪ : EnrichedEdgeCoch c) (s t : Fin 3) :
    cupOpp_param c őĪ (incidT c j m) s t m' = false := by
  unfold cupOpp_param diag_pair_param
  rw [incidT_layer_disjoint c j m m' h (pair_lo s) (pair_lo t)]
  rw [incidT_layer_disjoint c j m m' h (pair_hi s) (pair_hi t)]
  rw [incidT_layer_disjoint c j m m' h (pair_hi s) (pair_lo t)]
  rw [incidT_layer_disjoint c j m m' h (pair_lo s) (pair_hi t)]
  -- After rewrites the incidT-side factor is false; `_ && false`
  -- doesn't reduce by `rfl` (Bool.and matches first arg), so use
  -- explicit `Bool.and_false` rewrites.
  rw [Bool.and_false, Bool.and_false, Bool.and_false, Bool.and_false]
  rfl

theorem psi_layer_starCup_cross_layer (c : Nat) (i : Fin 3) (m m' : Fin c)
    (h : m.val ‚Č† m'.val) (ő≤ : EnrichedEdgeCoch c) :
    psi_layer c m' (cupOpp_param c (starS c i m) ő≤) = false := by
  unfold psi_layer
  rw [cupOpp_starS_cross_layer_zero c i m m' h ő≤ ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü©]
  rw [cupOpp_starS_cross_layer_zero c i m m' h ő≤ ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü©]
  rw [cupOpp_starS_cross_layer_zero c i m m' h ő≤ ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü©]
  rw [cupOpp_starS_cross_layer_zero c i m m' h ő≤ ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü©]
  rw [cupOpp_starS_cross_layer_zero c i m m' h ő≤ ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü©]
  rw [cupOpp_starS_cross_layer_zero c i m m' h ő≤ ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü©]
  rw [cupOpp_starS_cross_layer_zero c i m m' h ő≤ ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü©]
  rw [cupOpp_starS_cross_layer_zero c i m m' h ő≤ ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü©]
  rw [cupOpp_starS_cross_layer_zero c i m m' h ő≤ ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü©]
  rfl

theorem psi_layer_incidCup_cross_layer (c : Nat) (j : Fin 3) (m m' : Fin c)
    (h : m.val ‚Č† m'.val) (őĪ : EnrichedEdgeCoch c) :
    psi_layer c m' (cupOpp_param c őĪ (incidT c j m)) = false := by
  unfold psi_layer
  rw [cupOpp_incidT_cross_layer_zero c j m m' h őĪ ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü©]
  rw [cupOpp_incidT_cross_layer_zero c j m m' h őĪ ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü©]
  rw [cupOpp_incidT_cross_layer_zero c j m m' h őĪ ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü©]
  rw [cupOpp_incidT_cross_layer_zero c j m m' h őĪ ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü©]
  rw [cupOpp_incidT_cross_layer_zero c j m m' h őĪ ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü©]
  rw [cupOpp_incidT_cross_layer_zero c j m m' h őĪ ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü©]
  rw [cupOpp_incidT_cross_layer_zero c j m m' h őĪ ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®0, by decide‚ü©]
  rw [cupOpp_incidT_cross_layer_zero c j m m' h őĪ ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®1, by decide‚ü©]
  rw [cupOpp_incidT_cross_layer_zero c j m m' h őĪ ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü© ‚ü®2, by decide‚ü©]
  rfl

/-! ## ¬ß4.9 ‚ÄĒ Strengthened soundness (only on-layer kill required)

Combining `primary_cup_span_soundness_conditional` with the cross-layer
vanishing theorems above: the soundness `InPrimary ‚äÜ joint Ōą-kernel`
now only requires the **on-layer** kill `Ōą_m(starS i m ‚ą™ ő≤) = 0`
(and the T-analogue) for each `m`.  Cross-layer cases are dispatched
automatically by `psi_layer_starCup_cross_layer` /
`psi_layer_incidCup_cross_layer`.

This isolates Direction B's remaining work to a SINGLE conceptual
target: extend the bottom-layer kill to arbitrary `m`.  All
structural cross-layer reasoning is now closed. -/

theorem primary_cup_span_soundness_on_layer (c : Nat)
    (H_star_on : ‚ąÄ (i : Fin 3) (m : Fin c) (ő≤ : EnrichedEdgeCoch c),
        psi_layer c m (cupOpp_param c (starS c i m) ő≤) = false)
    (H_incid_on : ‚ąÄ (j : Fin 3) (m : Fin c) (őĪ : EnrichedEdgeCoch c),
        psi_layer c m (cupOpp_param c őĪ (incidT c j m)) = false) :
    ‚ąÄ v, InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary c v ‚Üí
      ‚ąÄ (m' : Fin c), psi_layer c m' v = false := by
  apply primary_cup_span_soundness_conditional c
  ¬∑ intro m' i m ő≤
    cases hmm : decide (m.val = m'.val) with
    | true =>
        have hm_eq : m.val = m'.val := of_decide_eq_true hmm
        have hm : m = m' := Fin.ext hm_eq
        rw [hm]
        exact H_star_on i m' ő≤
    | false =>
        have hm_ne : m.val ‚Č† m'.val := of_decide_eq_false hmm
        exact psi_layer_starCup_cross_layer c i m m' hm_ne ő≤
  ¬∑ intro m' j m őĪ
    cases hmm : decide (m.val = m'.val) with
    | true =>
        have hm_eq : m.val = m'.val := of_decide_eq_true hmm
        have hm : m = m' := Fin.ext hm_eq
        rw [hm]
        exact H_incid_on j m' őĪ
    | false =>
        have hm_ne : m.val ‚Č† m'.val := of_decide_eq_false hmm
        exact psi_layer_incidCup_cross_layer c j m m' hm_ne őĪ

/-! ## ¬ß4.10 ‚ÄĒ Unconditional all-c soundness

Chaining `primary_cup_span_soundness_on_layer` with
`parametric_arbitrary_m_full_kill_capstone` (Direction B's
arbitrary-m bilateral kill) discharges both on-layer hypotheses
`H_star_on` and `H_incid_on`.  Hence `InPrimary ‚äÜ joint Ōą-kernel`
holds UNCONDITIONALLY for every `c`, generalising
`primary_cup_span_soundness_c1` (¬ß4.7) from single-layer to
arbitrary multiplicity.

Closes the EASY direction (soundness) of the c-counter upper
bound at every Stern-Brocot position.  The matching HARD
direction (joint Ōą-kernel ‚äÜ InPrimary) remains an open piece,
reducible to the single-layer K_{3,3} dim count (`theory/RESEARCH_PLAN.md`
¬ß1.1).  -/

theorem primary_cup_span_soundness_all_c (c : Nat) :
    ‚ąÄ v, InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary c v ‚Üí
      ‚ąÄ (m' : Fin c), psi_layer c m' v = false := by
  apply primary_cup_span_soundness_on_layer c
  ¬∑ intro i m ő≤
    refine @fin3_cases
        (fun k => psi_layer c m (cupOpp_param c (starS c k m) ő≤) = false) ?_ ?_ ?_ i
    ¬∑ exact (parametric_arbitrary_m_full_kill_capstone c m).1 ő≤ |>.1
    ¬∑ exact (parametric_arbitrary_m_full_kill_capstone c m).1 ő≤ |>.2.1
    ¬∑ exact (parametric_arbitrary_m_full_kill_capstone c m).1 ő≤ |>.2.2
  ¬∑ intro j m őĪ
    refine @fin3_cases
        (fun k => psi_layer c m (cupOpp_param c őĪ (incidT c k m)) = false) ?_ ?_ ?_ j
    ¬∑ exact (parametric_arbitrary_m_full_kill_capstone c m).2 őĪ |>.1
    ¬∑ exact (parametric_arbitrary_m_full_kill_capstone c m).2 őĪ |>.2.1
    ¬∑ exact (parametric_arbitrary_m_full_kill_capstone c m).2 őĪ |>.2.2

/-! ## ¬ß5 ‚ÄĒ Conditional `codim ‚Č§ c` upper bound

Given the joint-Ōą-kernel hypothesis (`H_kernel_in_span`: every face
cochain killed by all c Ōą's lies in `InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary`),
every v decomposes ‚ÄĒ modulo `InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary` ‚ÄĒ as its
canonical `weighted_e_sum c (Ōą-vector v)` representative.

Corollary: the c Ōą-discriminators SPAN the dual of
`EnrichedFaceVal c / InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary`, matching the
parametric lower bound (`codim ‚Č• c`) and closing the c-counter
upper bound for the PRIMARY cup-image (the substantive sense in
which `codim = c`). -/

theorem codim_upper_bound_conditional (c : Nat)
    (H_kernel_in_span :
      ‚ąÄ r : EnrichedFaceVal c,
        (‚ąÄ m, psi_layer c m r = false) ‚Üí InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary c r) :
    ‚ąÄ v : EnrichedFaceVal c,
      InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary c (psi_residual c v)
      ‚ąß (‚ąÄ s t m', v s t m'
            = xor (weighted_e_sum c (fun m => psi_layer c m v) s t m')
                  (psi_residual c v s t m')) := by
  intro v
  refine ‚ü®H_kernel_in_span (psi_residual c v) (psi_residual_kills_all_psi c v), ?_‚ü©
  intro s t m'
  exact psi_canonical_decomposition c v s t m'

/-! ## ¬ß6 ‚ÄĒ Capstone: parametric dual-span (conditional)

The c functionals `(Ōą_0, ‚Ä¶, Ōą_{c-1})` are linearly independent
(established in `V33EnrichedParametric` via the dual basis
`e_face_layer m` with Kronecker-őī signature) and, conditionally
on the per-layer cup-image span hypothesis, span the dual of
`EnrichedFaceVal c / InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary`.

The hypothesis `H` reduces parametrically to a single per-layer
fact at K_{3,3}: the 9-element face space modulo (im őī¬Ļ +
primary cup-image) has dim 1.  Layer-disjointness of őī¬Ļ and
the primary cup-image lifts this per-layer fact to the c-layer
parametric statement. -/

theorem parametric_dual_span_capstone (c : Nat)
    (H : ‚ąÄ r : EnrichedFaceVal c,
      (‚ąÄ m, psi_layer c m r = false) ‚Üí InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary c r) :
    ‚ąÄ v : EnrichedFaceVal c, ‚ąÉ b : Fin c ‚Üí Bool,
      (‚ąÄ m, b m = psi_layer c m v)
      ‚ąß InPrimaryCupSpanPlusBoundary c (psi_residual c v)
      ‚ąß (‚ąÄ s t m', v s t m'
            = xor (weighted_e_sum c b s t m') (psi_residual c v s t m')) := by
  intro v
  refine ‚ü®fun m => psi_layer c m v, ?_, ?_, ?_‚ü©
  ¬∑ intro _; rfl
  ¬∑ exact H (psi_residual c v) (psi_residual_kills_all_psi c v)
  ¬∑ intro s t m'
    exact psi_canonical_decomposition c v s t m'

end E213.Lib.Math.Cohomology.Bipartite.V33EnrichedParametricDualSpan
